com.mojang.datafixers.optics

Interface Prism<S,T,A,B>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - The input object type.
    T - The output object type.
    A - The input field type.
    B - The output field type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Prism<S::A,T::B>, Optic<Cocartesian _,S::A,T::B>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Inj1, Inj2, InjTagged

    public interface Prism<S,T,A,B>
extends Optic<Cocartesian _,S::A,T::B>
    A prism is an optic that provides pattern matching against and construction from a field. It provides functionality to extract a value A from the input sum type S and to build an object of sum type T from a derived value B.

    The canonical example for using a prism is to extract and update a field of a tagged union type, using the C meaning of union.

    In order to be a lawful prism, the implementations of match(Object) and build(Object) must satisfy certain requirements. Assume that the object types S and T are implicitly convertible between each other and that the field types A and B are similarly convertible. Then the following rules must hold (== here represents logical equality and not reference equality).

    1. match(build(b)) == Right(b) - Matching against a built value yields that value.
    2. build?(match(s)) == s - If a field is matched, building with it yields the original object.

    Prisms that are not lawful are said to be either neutral or chaotic, depending on the degree to which the prism laws are broken.

    Type Shape:
    %.Type.[%0::%2,%1::%3]
    See Also:
    Union Types

    • Method Detail

      • match

        (T|A) match(S s)
        Attempts to extract the input field from the input object. Returns the straightforward transformation of the input object to the output object if the input field is not present.

        For example, say that the input object type is DataResult and the output object type is Optional. Calling match with the data result will return either the value present in the result (if a DataResult is a success), or an absent Optional (if the result is an error).

        Implementation Requirements:
        The implementation must, in conjunction with build(Object), satisfy the prism laws in order for this prism to be a lawful prism.
        Parameters:
        s - A value of the input object type from which to attempt to extract the input field value.
        Returns:
        Either the value of the input field, or a value of the output object type equivalent to the input.

      • build

        T build(B b)
        Constructs a value of the output object type with the given output field value.

        For example, this may be used to construct an Optional or DataResult from a plain value.

        Implementation Requirements:
        The implementation must, in conjunction with match(Object), satisfy the prism laws in order for this prism to be a lawful prism.
        Parameters:
        b - The value to construct the output object from.
        Returns:
        A value of the output object type that contains the output field.

      • eval

        default <P extends K2> (P<A,B>) -> P<S,T> eval(Cocartesian P proof)
        Evaluates this prism to produce a function that, when given a transformation between field types, produces a transformation between object types. The transformation matches the input object against the input field, and either builds an output object from the extracted value or returns the converted input.
        Specified by:
        eval in interface Optic<Cocartesian _,S::A,T::B>
        Type Parameters:
        P - The type associated with the profunctor.
        Parameters:
        proof - The Cocartesian type class instance for the transformation type.
        Returns:
        A function that takes a transformation between field types and produces a transformation between object types.

        Prism.Instance
